# Doc Layering

Read docs/STATE.md FIRST before starting work in a new session.

File responsibilities (do not mix layers):
- docs/STATE.md        : current-state snapshot. Overwrite in place. No history,
                         no rhetoric.
- docs/DECISIONS.md    : decision log (ADR). Append-only. Never rewrite/delete an
                         old entry's reasoning; only flip its Status line.
- docs/project-kickoff.md (local only, gitignored): owner's private product
                         vision / user-flow notes. Not in the remote repo; may
                         exist only on the maintainer's machine.
- packages/shared + code : machine contracts, the final source of truth.

Conflict priority: code/git > STATE.md > DECISIONS.md > local kickoff (if present).

Do NOT write technical decisions into local kickoff (they go in DECISIONS).
Do NOT write progress or debt into local kickoff (they go in STATE).
